<item>
            <title>[FLUME-2083] Avro Source should not start if SSL is enabled and keystore cannot be opened</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-2083</link>
                <project id="12311321" key="FLUME">Flume</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A couple of follow-up items from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-997&quot; title=&quot;Support secure transport mechanism&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLUME-997&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLUME-997&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. If the server is configured for SSL but the keystore isn&apos;t there, the service should not start.&lt;br/&gt;
2. We should fall back to the default behavior of the X509 TrustManagerFactory if there is no trust store specified by passing a null KeyStore, no need to look in the classpath for cacerts.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12652572">FLUME-2083</key>
            <summary>Avro Source should not start if SSL is enabled and keystore cannot be opened</summary>
